To find the value of $f(5)$, we must substitute $x=5$ into the given function definition.

First, identify the function: $f(x) = \dfrac{x+1}{3x-4}$ -> Next, substitute $x=5$ into the numerator and the denominator: $f(5) = \dfrac{5+1}{3(5)-4}$ -> Simplify the numerator: $5 + 1 = 6$ -> Simplify the denominator: $3(5) - 4 = 15 - 4 = 11$ -> Combine the simplified parts to form the final fraction: $f(5) = \dfrac{6}{11}$.

